{"questionId":"1251405","questionHtml":"<p>A satellite of mass <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math> orbits a planet of mass <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math> in a circular orbit of radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math>. What is the work that must be done on the satellite to increase its orbital radius to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>r</mi></math>?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"1251405","referenceCode":"21N.1A.HL.TZ0.32","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"A satellite of mass m orbits a planet of mass M in a circular orbit of radius r. What is the work that must be done on the satellite to increase its orbital radius to 2r? A. GMmr B","paper":"1A","level":"HL","questionNumber":"32","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["D. Fields","D.1 Gravitational fields"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}